Practical slow-motion effect:
```typescript
class SlowMotionEffect {
    private static readonly SLOW_SCALE = 0.3;
    private static readonly NORMAL_SCALE = 1.0;

    static activate(duration: number): void {
        const scheduler = cc.director.getScheduler();
        scheduler.setTimeScale(SlowMotionEffect.SLOW_SCALE);

        // Use real-time delay (not affected by time scale)
        setTimeout(() => {
            scheduler.setTimeScale(SlowMotionEffect.NORMAL_SCALE);
        }, duration * 1000);
    }
}

// Trigger 2-second slow motion on kill
SlowMotionEffect.activate(2.0);
```

Note: `setTimeScale` affects ALL scheduled callbacks and actions globally. Use `setTimeout` for real-time delays when time scale is altered.

Access the ActionManager via `cc.director.getActionManager()`:

```typescript
