`startAnimation` and `stopAnimation` control the main loop:

```typescript
// Stop the main loop (stops rendering and updates)
cc.director.stopAnimation();

// Restart the main loop
cc.director.startAnimation();
```

These are lower-level than `pause()`/`resume()`. Stopping animation completely halts the game loop:

```typescript
// Difference from pause:
// pause() — stops scheduler and actions, continues rendering
// stopAnimation() — stops everything including rendering

// Use case: app going to background
class AppLifecycle {
    static onEnterBackground(): void {
        cc.director.stopAnimation();
        cc.log('App backgrounded, animation stopped');
    }

    static onEnterForeground(): void {
        cc.director.startAnimation();
        cc.log('App foregrounded, animation resumed');
    }
}

// Use case: power saving when idle
class IdleDetector {
    private _idleTime: number = 0;
    private static readonly IDLE_THRESHOLD = 30; // seconds
    private _animationStopped: boolean = false;

    update(dt: number): void {
        this._idleTime += dt;
        if (this._idleTime > IdleDetector.IDLE_THRESHOLD && !this._animationStopped) {
            cc.director.stopAnimation();
            this._animationStopped = true;
        }
    }

    onUserInput(): void {
        this._idleTime = 0;
        if (this._animationStopped) {
            cc.director.startAnimation();
            this._animationStopped = false;
        }
    }
}
```

